{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc9de6772-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s425b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"425b"},"text":"§ 425b.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Receipt of project water by lessees of irrigable lands owned by States, etc.; time limitation; applicability of acreage limitations","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Lessees of irrigable lands owned by States, political subdivisions, and agencies thereof which are held to be subject to the acreage limitation provisions of Federal reclamation law and for which recordable contracts to sell have not been made may receive project water from ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1970","children":[],"tail":", subject to the same acreage limitation provisions of Federal reclamation law as private landowners."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc9de6773-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/310/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–310, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-07-07"},"text":"July 7, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/411"},"text":"84 Stat. 411","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/293/tII/s224/d"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–293, title II, § 224(d)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1982-10-12"},"text":"Oct. 12, 1982","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/96/1272"},"text":"96 Stat. 1272","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc9de6774-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc9de6775-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc9de6776-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Federal reclamation law, referred to in text, probably means ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1902-06-17/ch1093"},"text":"act June 17, 1902, ch. 1093","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/32/388"},"text":"32 Stat. 388","children":[],"tail":", and Acts amendatory thereof and supplementary thereto. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s425"},"text":"section 425 of this title","children":[],"tail":". Act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1902-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1902","children":[],"tail":", popularly known as the Reclamation Act, is classified generally to this chapter. For complete classification of act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1902-06-17"},"text":"June 17, 1902","children":[],"tail":", to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t43/s371"},"text":"section 371 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idc9de6777-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1982—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/97/293"},"text":"Pub. L. 97–293","children":[],"tail":" struck out “for a period not to exceed twenty-five years” after “may receive project water”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
